306 // Helpers: Bit manipulation
307 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
308 static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
309 static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

342 // Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
343 // We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
344 // We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
345 #ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
346 IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
347 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs, lhs.y * rhs); }
348 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs, lhs.y / rhs); }
349 static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y); }
350 static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y); }
351 static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
352 static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs.x, lhs.y / rhs.y); }
353 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
354 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
355 static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
356 static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
357 static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs.x; lhs.y *= rhs.y; return lhs; }
358 static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs.x; lhs.y /= rhs.y; return lhs; }
359 static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y, lhs.z + rhs.z, lhs.w + rhs.w); }
360 static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y, lhs.z - rhs.z, lhs.w - rhs.w); }
361 static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y, lhs.z * rhs.z, lhs.w * rhs.w); }
362 IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE
363 #endif

387 // Helpers: Maths
388 IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
389 // - Wrapper for standard libs functions. (Note that imgui_demo.cpp does _not_ use them to keep the code easy to copy)
390 #ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_MATH_FUNCTIONS
391 #define ImFabs(X) fabsf(X)
392 #define ImSqrt(X) sqrtf(X)
393 #define ImFmod(X, Y) fmodf((X), (Y))
394 #define ImCos(X) cosf(X)
395 #define ImSin(X) sinf(X)
396 #define ImAcos(X) acosf(X)
397 #define ImAtan2(Y, X) atan2f((Y), (X))
398 #define ImAtof(STR) atof(STR)
399 //#define ImFloorStd(X) floorf(X) // We use our own, see ImFloor() and ImFloorSigned()
400 #define ImCeil(X) ceilf(X)
401 static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
402 static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
403 static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
404 static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
405 static inline int ImAbs(int x) { return x < 0 ? -x : x; }
406 static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
407 static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
408 static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : ((x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f); } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
409 static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : ((x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0); }
410 #ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_SSE
411 static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return _mm_cvtss_f32(_mm_rsqrt_ss(_mm_set_ss(x))); }
412 #else
413 static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return 1.0f / sqrtf(x); }
414 #endif
415 static inline double ImRsqrt(double x) { return 1.0 / sqrt(x); }
416 #endif
417 // - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
418 // (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
419 template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
420 template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
421 template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
422 template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
423 template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
424 template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
425 template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
426 // - Misc maths helpers
427 static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
428 static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
429 static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
430 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
431 static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
432 static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
433 static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
434 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
435 static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
436 static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return ImRsqrt(d); return fail_value; }
437 static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
438 static inline float ImFloorSigned(float f) { return (float)((f >= 0 || (int)f == f) ? (int)f : (int)f - 1); } // Decent replacement for floorf()
439 static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
440 static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
441 static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
442 static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
443 static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
444 static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }

478 // Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
479 // NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
480 struct IMGUI_API ImRect
481 {
482  ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
483  ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
484 
485  ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
486  ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
487  ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
488  ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
489 
490  ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
491  ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
492  float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
493  float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
494  float GetArea() const { return (Max.x - Min.x) * (Max.y - Min.y); }
495  ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
496  ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
497  ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
498  ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
499  bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
500  bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
501  bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
502  void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
503  void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
504  void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
505  void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
506  void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
507  void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
508  void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
509  void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
510  void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
511  void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
512  bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
513  ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
514 };

517 // Helper: ImBitArray
518 inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
519 inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
520 inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
521 inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2) // Works on range [n..n2)
522 {
523  n2--;
524  while (n <= n2)
525  {
526  int a_mod = (n & 31);
527  int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
528  ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
529  arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
530  n = (n + 32) & ~31;
531  }
532 }
533 
534 // Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
535 // Store 1-bit per value.
536 template<int BITCOUNT>
537 struct IMGUI_API ImBitArray
538 {
539  ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
540  ImBitArray() { ClearAllBits(); }
541  void ClearAllBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
542  void SetAllBits() { memset(Storage, 255, sizeof(Storage)); }
543  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
544  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
545  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
546  void SetBitRange(int n, int n2) { ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n, n2); } // Works on range [n..n2)
547 };
548 
549 // Helper: ImBitVector
550 // Store 1-bit per value.
551 struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
552 {
553  ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
554  void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
555  void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
556  bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
557  void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
558  void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
559 };

561 // Helper: ImSpan<>
562 // Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
563 template<typename T>
564 struct ImSpan
565 {
566  T* Data;
567  T* DataEnd;
568 
569  // Constructors, destructor
570  inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
571  inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
572  inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
573 
574  inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
575  inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
576  inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
577  inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
578  inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
579  inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
580 
581  inline T* begin() { return Data; }
582  inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
583  inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
584  inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
585 
586  // Utilities
587  inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
588 };
589 
590 // Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
591 // Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
592 // - Usage: call Reserve() N times, allocate GetArenaSizeInBytes() worth, pass it to SetArenaBasePtr(), call GetSpan() N times to retrieve the aligned ranges.
593 template<int CHUNKS>
594 struct ImSpanAllocator
595 {
596  char* BasePtr;
597  int CurrOff;
598  int CurrIdx;
599  int Offsets[CHUNKS];
600  int Sizes[CHUNKS];
601 
602  ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
603  inline void Reserve(int n, size_t sz, int a=4) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrIdx && n < CHUNKS); CurrOff = IM_MEMALIGN(CurrOff, a); Offsets[n] = CurrOff; Sizes[n] = (int)sz; CurrIdx++; CurrOff += (int)sz; }
604  inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return CurrOff; }
605  inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
606  inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
607  inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n] + Sizes[n]); }
608  template<typename T>
609  inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
610 };
611 
612 // Helper: ImPool<>
613 // Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
614 // Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
615 typedef int ImPoolIdx;
616 template<typename T>
617 struct IMGUI_API ImPool
618 {
619  ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
620  ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
621  ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
622  ImPoolIdx AliveCount; // Number of active/alive items (for display purpose)
623 
624  ImPool() { FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
625  ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
626  T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
627  T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
628  ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
629  T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
630  bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
631  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
632  T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); AliveCount++; return &Buf[idx]; }
633  void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
634  void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); AliveCount--; }
635  void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
636 
637  // To iterate a ImPool: for (int n = 0; n < pool.GetMapSize(); n++) if (T* t = pool.TryGetMapData(n)) { ... }
638  // Can be avoided if you know .Remove() has never been called on the pool, or AliveCount == GetMapSize()
639  int GetAliveCount() const { return AliveCount; } // Number of active/alive items in the pool (for display purpose)
640  int GetBufSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
641  int GetMapSize() const { return Map.Data.Size; } // It is the map we need iterate to find valid items, since we don't have "alive" storage anywhere
642  T* TryGetMapData(ImPoolIdx n) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx == -1) return NULL; return GetByIndex(idx); }
643 #ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
644  int GetSize() { return GetMapSize(); } // For ImPlot: should use GetMapSize() from (IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18304)
645 #endif
646 };
647 
648 // Helper: ImChunkStream<>
649 // Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
650 // This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
651 // We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries.
652 // The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
653 template<typename T>
654 struct IMGUI_API ImChunkStream
655 {
656  ImVector<char> Buf;
657 
658  void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
659  bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
660  int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
661  T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = IM_MEMALIGN(HDR_SZ + sz, 4u); int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
662  T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
663  T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
664  int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
665  T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
666  int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
667  T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
668  void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
669 
670 };

672 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
673 // [SECTION] ImDrawList support
674 //-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
675 
676 // ImDrawList: Helper function to calculate a circle's segment count given its radius and a "maximum error" value.
677 // Estimation of number of circle segment based on error is derived using method described in https://stackoverflow.com/a/2244088/15194693
678 // Number of segments (N) is calculated using equation:
679 // N = ceil ( pi / acos(1 - error / r) ) where r > 0, error <= r
680 // Our equation is significantly simpler that one in the post thanks for choosing segment that is
681 // perpendicular to X axis. Follow steps in the article from this starting condition and you will
682 // will get this result.
683 //
684 // Rendering circles with an odd number of segments, while mathematically correct will produce
685 // asymmetrical results on the raster grid. Therefore we're rounding N to next even number (7->8, 8->8, 9->10 etc.)
686 //
687 #define IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN(_V) ((((_V) + 1) / 2) * 2)
688 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN 4
689 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX 512
690 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC(_RAD,_MAXERROR) ImClamp(IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN((int)ImCeil(IM_PI / ImAcos(1 - ImMin((_MAXERROR), (_RAD)) / (_RAD)))), IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN, IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX)
691 
692 // Raw equation from IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC rewritten for 'r' and 'error'.
693 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_R(_N,_MAXERROR) ((_MAXERROR) / (1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))))
694 #define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_ERROR(_N,_RAD) ((1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))) / (_RAD))
695 
696 // ImDrawList: Lookup table size for adaptive arc drawing, cover full circle.
697 #ifndef IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE
698 #define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE 48 // Number of samples in lookup table.
699 #endif
700 #define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_SAMPLE_MAX IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE // Sample index _PathArcToFastEx() for 360 angle.
701 
702 // Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
703 // You may want to create your own instance of this if you want to use ImDrawList completely without ImGui. In that case, watch out for future changes to this structure.
704 struct IMGUI_API ImDrawListSharedData
705 {
706  ImVec2 TexUvWhitePixel; // UV of white pixel in the atlas
707  ImFont* Font; // Current/default font (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
708  float FontSize; // Current/default font size (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
709  float CurveTessellationTol; // Tessellation tolerance when using PathBezierCurveTo()
710  float CircleSegmentMaxError; // Number of circle segments to use per pixel of radius for AddCircle() etc
711  ImVec4 ClipRectFullscreen; // Value for PushClipRectFullscreen()
712  ImDrawListFlags InitialFlags; // Initial flags at the beginning of the frame (it is possible to alter flags on a per-drawlist basis afterwards)
713 
714  // [Internal] Lookup tables
715  ImVec2 ArcFastVtx[IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE]; // Sample points on the quarter of the circle.
716  float ArcFastRadiusCutoff; // Cutoff radius after which arc drawing will fallback to slower PathArcTo()
717  ImU8 CircleSegmentCounts[64]; // Precomputed segment count for given radius before we calculate it dynamically (to avoid calculation overhead)
718  const ImVec4* TexUvLines; // UV of anti-aliased lines in the atlas
719 
720  ImDrawListSharedData();
721  void SetCircleTessellationMaxError(float max_error);
722 };
723 
724 struct ImDrawDataBuilder
725 {
726  ImVector<ImDrawList*> Layers[2]; // Global layers for: regular, tooltip
727 
728  void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].resize(0); }
729  void ClearFreeMemory() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].clear(); }
730  int GetDrawListCount() const { int count = 0; for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) count += Layers[n].Size; return count; }
731  IMGUI_API void FlattenIntoSingleLayer();
732 };

738 // Transient per-window flags, reset at the beginning of the frame. For child window, inherited from parent on first Begin().
739 // This is going to be exposed in imgui.h when stabilized enough.
740 enum ImGuiItemFlags_
741 {
742  ImGuiItemFlags_None = 0,
743  ImGuiItemFlags_NoTabStop = 1 << 0, // false // Disable keyboard tabbing (FIXME: should merge with _NoNav)
744  ImGuiItemFlags_ButtonRepeat = 1 << 1, // false // Button() will return true multiple times based on io.KeyRepeatDelay and io.KeyRepeatRate settings.
745  ImGuiItemFlags_Disabled = 1 << 2, // false // Disable interactions but doesn't affect visuals. See BeginDisabled()/EndDisabled(). See github.com/ocornut/imgui/issues/211
746  ImGuiItemFlags_NoNav = 1 << 3, // false // Disable keyboard/gamepad directional navigation (FIXME: should merge with _NoTabStop)
747  ImGuiItemFlags_NoNavDefaultFocus = 1 << 4, // false // Disable item being a candidate for default focus (e.g. used by title bar items)
748  ImGuiItemFlags_SelectableDontClosePopup = 1 << 5, // false // Disable MenuItem/Selectable() automatically closing their popup window
749  ImGuiItemFlags_MixedValue = 1 << 6, // false // [BETA] Represent a mixed/indeterminate value, generally multi-selection where values differ. Currently only supported by Checkbox() (later should support all sorts of widgets)
750  ImGuiItemFlags_ReadOnly = 1 << 7 // false // [ALPHA] Allow hovering interactions but underlying value is not changed.
751 };

1060 // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
1061 // For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
1062 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
1063 {
1064  ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
1065  int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
1066  ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
1067  ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
1068  ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
1069  bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
1070  int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
1071  float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
1072  ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
1073  float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
1074  bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
1075  bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
1076  bool Edited; // edited this frame
1077  ImGuiInputTextFlags Flags; // copy of InputText() flags
1078  ImGuiInputTextCallback UserCallback; // "
1079  void* UserCallbackData; // "
1080 
1081  ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1082  void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
1083  void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
1084  int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
1085  int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
1086  void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
1087 
1088  // Cursor & Selection
1089  void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
1090  void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
1091  bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
1092  void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
1093  int GetCursorPos() const { return Stb.cursor; }
1094  int GetSelectionStart() const { return Stb.select_start; }
1095  int GetSelectionEnd() const { return Stb.select_end; }
1096  void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
1097 };

1291 
1292 // ImGuiViewport Private/Internals fields (cardinal sin: we are using inheritance!)
1293 // Every instance of ImGuiViewport is in fact a ImGuiViewportP.
1294 struct ImGuiViewportP : public ImGuiViewport
1295 {
1296  int DrawListsLastFrame[2]; // Last frame number the background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists were used
1297  ImDrawList* DrawLists[2]; // Convenience background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists. We use them to draw software mouser cursor when io.MouseDrawCursor is set and to draw most debug overlays.
1298  ImDrawData DrawDataP;
1299  ImDrawDataBuilder DrawDataBuilder;
1300 
1301  ImVec2 WorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset from Pos to top-left corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,+main_menu_bar_height). Work Area is Full Area but without menu-bars/status-bars (so WorkArea always fit inside Pos/Size!)
1302  ImVec2 WorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset from Pos+Size to bottom-right corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,-status_bar_height).
1303  ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally >= 0.0f.
1304  ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally <= 0.0f.
1305 
1306  ImGuiViewportP() { DrawListsLastFrame[0] = DrawListsLastFrame[1] = -1; DrawLists[0] = DrawLists[1] = NULL; }
1307  ~ImGuiViewportP() { if (DrawLists[0]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[0]); if (DrawLists[1]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[1]); }
1308 
1309  // Calculate work rect pos/size given a set of offset (we have 1 pair of offset for rect locked from last frame data, and 1 pair for currently building rect)
1310  ImVec2 CalcWorkRectPos(const ImVec2& off_min) const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + off_min.x, Pos.y + off_min.y); }
1311  ImVec2 CalcWorkRectSize(const ImVec2& off_min, const ImVec2& off_max) const { return ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, Size.x - off_min.x + off_max.x), ImMax(0.0f, Size.y - off_min.y + off_max.y)); }
1312  void UpdateWorkRect() { WorkPos = CalcWorkRectPos(WorkOffsetMin); WorkSize = CalcWorkRectSize(WorkOffsetMin, WorkOffsetMax); } // Update public fields
1313 
1314  // Helpers to retrieve ImRect (we don't need to store BuildWorkRect as every access tend to change it, hence the code asymmetry)
1315  ImRect GetMainRect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1316  ImRect GetWorkRect() const { return ImRect(WorkPos.x, WorkPos.y, WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y); }
1317  ImRect GetBuildWorkRect() const { ImVec2 pos = CalcWorkRectPos(BuildWorkOffsetMin); ImVec2 size = CalcWorkRectSize(BuildWorkOffsetMin, BuildWorkOffsetMax); return ImRect(pos.x, pos.y, pos.x + size.x, pos.y + size.y); }
1318 };

1820 // Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
1821 // (That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered..)
1822 // (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
1823 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
1824 {
1825  // Layout
1826  ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
1827  ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
1828  ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
1829  ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSize at the beginning of next frame, for scrolling range and auto-resize. Always growing during the frame.
1830  ImVec2 IdealMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSizeIdeal at the beginning of next frame, for auto-resize only. Always growing during the frame.
1831  ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
1832  ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
1833  float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
1834  float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
1835  ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
1836  ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
1837  ImVec1 GroupOffset;
1838 
1839  // Keyboard/Gamepad navigation
1840  ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
1841  short NavLayersActiveMask; // Which layers have been written to (result from previous frame)
1842  short NavLayersActiveMaskNext;// Which layers have been written to (accumulator for current frame)
1843  ImGuiID NavFocusScopeIdCurrent; // Current focus scope ID while appending
1844  bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
1845  bool NavHasScroll; // Set when scrolling can be used (ScrollMax > 0.0f)
1846 
1847  // Miscellaneous
1848  bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
1849  ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
1850  ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement
1851  int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
1852  ImU32 TreeJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
1853  ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
1854  ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
1855  ImGuiOldColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
1856  int CurrentTableIdx; // Current table index (into g.Tables)
1857  ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
1858  ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
1859  int FocusCounterRegular; // (Legacy Focus/Tabbing system) Sequential counter, start at -1 and increase as assigned via FocusableItemRegister() (FIXME-NAV: Needs redesign)
1860  int FocusCounterTabStop; // (Legacy Focus/Tabbing system) Same, but only count widgets which you can Tab through.
1861 
1862  // Local parameters stacks
1863  // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
1864  float ItemWidth; // Current item width (>0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window).
1865  float TextWrapPos; // Current text wrap pos.
1866  ImVector<float> ItemWidthStack; // Store item widths to restore (attention: .back() is not == ItemWidth)
1867  ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack; // Store text wrap pos to restore (attention: .back() is not == TextWrapPos)
1868  ImGuiStackSizes StackSizesOnBegin; // Store size of various stacks for asserting
1869 };

1871 // Storage for one window
1872 struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
1873 {
1874  char* Name; // Window name, owned by the window.
1875  ImGuiID ID; // == ImHashStr(Name)
1876  ImGuiWindowFlags Flags; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
1877  ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)
1878  ImVec2 Size; // Current size (==SizeFull or collapsed title bar size)
1879  ImVec2 SizeFull; // Size when non collapsed
1880  ImVec2 ContentSize; // Size of contents/scrollable client area (calculated from the extents reach of the cursor) from previous frame. Does not include window decoration or window padding.
1881  ImVec2 ContentSizeIdeal;
1882  ImVec2 ContentSizeExplicit; // Size of contents/scrollable client area explicitly request by the user via SetNextWindowContentSize().
1883  ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().
1884  float WindowRounding; // Window rounding at the time of Begin(). May be clamped lower to avoid rendering artifacts with title bar, menu bar etc.
1885  float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().
1886  int NameBufLen; // Size of buffer storing Name. May be larger than strlen(Name)!
1887  ImGuiID MoveId; // == window->GetID("#MOVE")
1888  ImGuiID ChildId; // ID of corresponding item in parent window (for navigation to return from child window to parent window)
1889  ImVec2 Scroll;
1890  ImVec2 ScrollMax;
1891  ImVec2 ScrollTarget; // target scroll position. stored as cursor position with scrolling canceled out, so the highest point is always 0.0f. (FLT_MAX for no change)
1892  ImVec2 ScrollTargetCenterRatio; // 0.0f = scroll so that target position is at top, 0.5f = scroll so that target position is centered
1893  ImVec2 ScrollTargetEdgeSnapDist; // 0.0f = no snapping, >0.0f snapping threshold
1894  ImVec2 ScrollbarSizes; // Size taken by each scrollbars on their smaller axis. Pay attention! ScrollbarSizes.x == width of the vertical scrollbar, ScrollbarSizes.y = height of the horizontal scrollbar.
1895  bool ScrollbarX, ScrollbarY; // Are scrollbars visible?
1896  bool Active; // Set to true on Begin(), unless Collapsed
1897  bool WasActive;
1898  bool WriteAccessed; // Set to true when any widget access the current window
1899  bool Collapsed; // Set when collapsing window to become only title-bar
1900  bool WantCollapseToggle;
1901  bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
1902  bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
1903  bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
1904  bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
1905  bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
1906  signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
1907  short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
1908  short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Begin() order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
1909  short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Begin() order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
1910  short FocusOrder; // Order within WindowsFocusOrder[], altered when windows are focused.
1911  ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
1912  ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
1913  ImS8 AutoFitChildAxises;
1914  bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
1915  ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
1916  ImS8 HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
1917  ImS8 HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
1918  ImS8 HiddenFramesForRenderOnly; // Hide the window until frame N at Render() time only
1919  ImS8 DisableInputsFrames; // Disable window interactions for N frames
1920  ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
1921  ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
1922  ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.
1923  ImVec2 SetWindowPosVal; // store window position when using a non-zero Pivot (position set needs to be processed when we know the window size)
1924  ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
1925 
1926  ImVector<ImGuiID> IDStack; // ID stack. ID are hashes seeded with the value at the top of the stack. (In theory this should be in the TempData structure)
1927  ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
1928 
1929  // The best way to understand what those rectangles are is to use the 'Metrics->Tools->Show Windows Rectangles' viewer.
1930  // The main 'OuterRect', omitted as a field, is window->Rect().
1931  ImRect OuterRectClipped; // == Window->Rect() just after setup in Begin(). == window->Rect() for root window.
1932  ImRect InnerRect; // Inner rectangle (omit title bar, menu bar, scroll bar)
1933  ImRect InnerClipRect; // == InnerRect shrunk by WindowPadding*0.5f on each side, clipped within viewport or parent clip rect.
1934  ImRect WorkRect; // Initially covers the whole scrolling region. Reduced by containers e.g columns/tables when active. Shrunk by WindowPadding*1.0f on each side. This is meant to replace ContentRegionRect over time (from 1.71+ onward).
1935  ImRect ParentWorkRect; // Backup of WorkRect before entering a container such as columns/tables. Used by e.g. SpanAllColumns functions to easily access. Stacked containers are responsible for maintaining this. // FIXME-WORKRECT: Could be a stack?
1936  ImRect ClipRect; // Current clipping/scissoring rectangle, evolve as we are using PushClipRect(), etc. == DrawList->clip_rect_stack.back().
1937  ImRect ContentRegionRect; // FIXME: This is currently confusing/misleading. It is essentially WorkRect but not handling of scrolling. We currently rely on it as right/bottom aligned sizing operation need some size to rely on.
1938  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleSize; // Define an optional rectangular hole where mouse will pass-through the window.
1939  ImVec2ih HitTestHoleOffset;
1940 
1941  int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the window was Active.
1942  float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp the window was Active (using float as we don't need high precision there)
1943  float ItemWidthDefault;
1944  ImGuiStorage StateStorage;
1945  ImVector<ImGuiOldColumns> ColumnsStorage;
1946  float FontWindowScale; // User scale multiplier per-window, via SetWindowFontScale()
1947  int SettingsOffset; // Offset into SettingsWindows[] (offsets are always valid as we only grow the array from the back)
1948 
1949  ImDrawList* DrawList; // == &DrawListInst (for backward compatibility reason with code using imgui_internal.h we keep this a pointer)
1950  ImDrawList DrawListInst;
1951  ImGuiWindow* ParentWindow; // If we are a child _or_ popup window, this is pointing to our parent. Otherwise NULL.
1952  ImGuiWindow* RootWindow; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window == Top-level window.
1953  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which will display TitleBgActive color when this window is active.
1954  ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForNav; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which doesn't have the NavFlattened flag.
1955 
1956  ImGuiWindow* NavLastChildNavWindow; // When going to the menu bar, we remember the child window we came from. (This could probably be made implicit if we kept g.Windows sorted by last focused including child window.)
1957  ImGuiID NavLastIds[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Last known NavId for this window, per layer (0/1)
1958  ImRect NavRectRel[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Reference rectangle, in window relative space
1959 
1960  int MemoryDrawListIdxCapacity; // Backup of last idx/vtx count, so when waking up the window we can preallocate and avoid iterative alloc/copy
1961  int MemoryDrawListVtxCapacity;
1962  bool MemoryCompacted; // Set when window extraneous data have been garbage collected
1963 
1964 public:
1965  ImGuiWindow(ImGuiContext* context, const char* name);
1966  ~ImGuiWindow();
1967 
1968  ImGuiID GetID(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
1969  ImGuiID GetID(const void* ptr);
1970  ImGuiID GetID(int n);
1971  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
1972  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(const void* ptr);
1973  ImGuiID GetIDNoKeepAlive(int n);
1974  ImGuiID GetIDFromRectangle(const ImRect& r_abs);
1975 
1976  // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWidow.
1977  ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1978  float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
1979  float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }
1980  ImRect TitleBarRect() const { return ImRect(Pos, ImVec2(Pos.x + SizeFull.x, Pos.y + TitleBarHeight())); }
1981  float MenuBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? DC.MenuBarOffset.y + CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f : 0.0f; }
1982  ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }
1983 };

1999 {
2000  ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_ = ImGuiTabItemFlags_Leading | ImGuiTabItemFlags_Trailing,
2001  ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 20, // Track whether p_open was set or not (we'll need this info on the next frame to recompute ContentWidth during layout)
2002  ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button = 1 << 21 // Used by TabItemButton, change the tab item behavior to mimic a button
2003 };

2005 // Storage for one active tab item (sizeof() 40 bytes)
2006 struct ImGuiTabItem
2007 {
2008  ImGuiID ID;
2009  ImGuiTabItemFlags Flags;
2010  int LastFrameVisible;
2011  int LastFrameSelected; // This allows us to infer an ordered list of the last activated tabs with little maintenance
2012  float Offset; // Position relative to beginning of tab
2013  float Width; // Width currently displayed
2014  float ContentWidth; // Width of label, stored during BeginTabItem() call
2015  ImS32 NameOffset; // When Window==NULL, offset to name within parent ImGuiTabBar::TabsNames
2016  ImS16 BeginOrder; // BeginTabItem() order, used to re-order tabs after toggling ImGuiTabBarFlags_Reorderable
2017  ImS16 IndexDuringLayout; // Index only used during TabBarLayout()
2018  bool WantClose; // Marked as closed by SetTabItemClosed()

2079 // [Internal] sizeof() ~ 104
2080 // We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
2081 // We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
2082 // This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".
2083 struct ImGuiTableColumn
2084 {
2085  ImGuiTableColumnFlags Flags; // Flags after some patching (not directly same as provided by user). See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
2086  float WidthGiven; // Final/actual width visible == (MaxX - MinX), locked in TableUpdateLayout(). May be > WidthRequest to honor minimum width, may be < WidthRequest to honor shrinking columns down in tight space.
2087  float MinX; // Absolute positions
2088  float MaxX;
2089  float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
2090  float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
2091  float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
2092  float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
2093  ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column
2094  ImGuiID UserID; // Optional, value passed to TableSetupColumn()
2095  float WorkMinX; // Contents region min ~(MinX + CellPaddingX + CellSpacingX1) == cursor start position when entering column
2096  float WorkMaxX; // Contents region max ~(MaxX - CellPaddingX - CellSpacingX2)
2097  float ItemWidth; // Current item width for the column, preserved across rows
2098  float ContentMaxXFrozen; // Contents maximum position for frozen rows (apart from headers), from which we can infer content width.
2099  float ContentMaxXUnfrozen;
2100  float ContentMaxXHeadersUsed; // Contents maximum position for headers rows (regardless of freezing). TableHeader() automatically softclip itself + report ideal desired size, to avoid creating extraneous draw calls
2101  float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
2102  ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]
2103  ImGuiTableColumnIdx DisplayOrder; // Index within Table's IndexToDisplayOrder[] (column may be reordered by users)
2104  ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
2105  ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
2106  ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column
2107  ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortOrder; // Index of this column within sort specs, -1 if not sorting on this column, 0 for single-sort, may be >0 on multi-sort
2108  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelCurrent; // Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2109  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelFrozen; // Draw channels for frozen rows (often headers)
2110  ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelUnfrozen; // Draw channels for unfrozen rows
2111  bool IsEnabled; // IsUserEnabled && (Flags & ImGuiTableColumnFlags_Disabled) == 0
2112  bool IsUserEnabled; // Is the column not marked Hidden by the user? (unrelated to being off view, e.g. clipped by scrolling).
2113  bool IsUserEnabledNextFrame;
2114  bool IsVisibleX; // Is actually in view (e.g. overlapping the host window clipping rectangle, not scrolled).
2115  bool IsVisibleY;
2116  bool IsRequestOutput; // Return value for TableSetColumnIndex() / TableNextColumn(): whether we request user to output contents or not.
2117  bool IsSkipItems; // Do we want item submissions to this column to be completely ignored (no layout will happen).
2118  bool IsPreserveWidthAuto;
2119  ImS8 NavLayerCurrent; // ImGuiNavLayer in 1 byte
2120  ImU8 AutoFitQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to request auto-fit
2121  ImU8 CannotSkipItemsQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to disable Clipped/SkipItem
2122  ImU8 SortDirection : 2; // ImGuiSortDirection_Ascending or ImGuiSortDirection_Descending
2123  ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailCount : 2; // Number of available sort directions (0 to 3)
2124  ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailMask : 4; // Mask of available sort directions (1-bit each)
2125  ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailList; // Ordered of available sort directions (2-bits each)
2126 
2127  ImGuiTableColumn()
2128  {
2129  memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));
2130  StretchWeight = WidthRequest = -1.0f;
2131  NameOffset = -1;
2132  DisplayOrder = IndexWithinEnabledSet = -1;
2133  PrevEnabledColumn = NextEnabledColumn = -1;
2134  SortOrder = -1;
2135  SortDirection = ImGuiSortDirection_None;
2136  DrawChannelCurrent = DrawChannelFrozen = DrawChannelUnfrozen = (ImU8)-1;
2137  }
2138 };

2427  // If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
2428  // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
2429  // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
2430  // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
2431  inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable flag to ItemAdd()
2432  inline IM_NORETURN void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
2433 #endif
